title: Jacobs Wins First Game at Tewksbury
title_page: Jacobs Wins First Game at Tewksbury
maintext:
Jacobs Wins First Game at Tewksbury
Zach Jacobs won his first game as Tewksbury High’s boys lacrosse coach, as the Redmen easily got past Lowell Catholic, 11-3, during a non-league meeting Wednesday.
Boys lacrosse
In other action, Hollis-Brookline topped Alvirne, 13-5.
Tewksbury 11
Lowell Catholic 3
Josh Sughrue collected 3 goals, while Derek Schumaker and Kyle Darrigo each notched 2 goals to power the Redmen.
Adding a goal each were Dylan Scott, Pat Rosemond, Jason Cooke and Colby Brown.
Shawsheen 14
Minuteman 3
Dan Lee sparked Shawsheen Tech’s potent offense with 2 goals and 3 assists.
Conor Looney netted 4 goals for the Rams (4-0).
Owen Sullivan and Dylan Timmons potted 3 goals each, while Dave Fraser scored 2 goals and had 1 assist.
Jonah Varallo (6 saves) earned the win in net.
Marblehead 10
Westford 7
Cam Barisano and Pressly Meade scored 2 goals each for Westford during this non-league game Tuesday.
Jason Bunyon and Matt Curran each notched a goal and assist, while Nate Arsenault fired home 1 goal.
Essex Tech 15
Nashoba Tech 2
Junior middie Matt Lucozzi scored both goals for the Vikings (1-2), while goalie Kyle Besjardin was superb in making 28 saves.
Hollis-Brookline 13
Alvirne 5
Despite a strong defensive performance in Hudson, the Broncos fell to Hollis-Brookline.
Dylan Bliss played a solid game for Alvirne and scored 2 goals.
Algonquin 17
Groton-Dunstable 2
Senior attack Nathan Townsend scored both goals in the losing effort. Also playing well was goalie Declan Nash, who turned away 14 shots.
